caption:
All Cybertruck models have the following characteristics: 250 kW Supercharge, spring suspension, 110 and 220 volt outlets, weight - 2700 kilograms, engine power - 775 hp]. The vehicles have a load-bearing body structure as opposed to a frame in conventional pickup trucks. Like all other Tesla vehicles, a stability system can be ordered by paying an additional $7,000 in the price of the entire configuration.
- Single motor RWD // range 482 km // acceleration 0-100 km/h less than 6.5 seconds // top speed 170 km/h // payload capacity 1587 kilograms // trailer weight 3400 kilograms // price $ 39,900 //
- Dual motor AWD // driving range 600 km // acceleration 0-100 km/h less than 4.5 seconds // top speed 193 km/h // payload 1587 kg // trailer weight more than 4535 kg // price 49 900 dollars //
- Tri motor AWD // range over 800 km // acceleration 0-100 km/h less than 2.9 seconds // top speed 210 km/h // payload 1587 kg // trailer over 6350 kg // price 69 900 dollars // //
Additionally, Tesla confirms the following dimensions for all models: trunk volume - 2.8 cubic meters. Trunk length - 198 cm. Ground clearance - up to 40 centimeters. Angle of approach - 35 degrees. Exit angle - 28 degrees.

The standard model will use a tweakable air suspension to compensate for variations in load and, it will also have all-wheel drive. It will have on-board inverters to support 110- and 220-volt outlets, allowing you to take advantage of the machine’s power without a portable generator. The air compressor needed for the air suspension is also present. Cameras in the car allow for automatic parallel parking.

Battery options allow you to change the range of travel from one full charge from 400 to 800 kilometers. Battery capacity is approximately 123 kWh[17]. The cabin can be protected against shrapnel and small fragments.

A fully pressurized cab is optionally available, which would allow the Cybertruck to be used as an amphibious vehicle.
